{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01YD6kBeH3bZstFp6snsNeYj","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The task is clear. I need to:\n1. Generate TLS certificates using openssl (via an openssl-toolbox pod)\n2. Store them as Kubernetes secrets\n3. Mount the certs into the CockroachDB pods\n4. Restart the cluster in secure mode (without `--insecure` flag)\n\nLet me plan this out:\n\n**Step 1: Create the openssl-toolbox pod**\nFirst, I need to create an openssl-toolbox pod to generate certificates.\n\n**Step 2: Generate certificates**\nCockroachDB needs:\n- A CA certificate (ca.crt, ca.key)\n- Node certificates for each pod (node.crt, node.key)\n- Client certificates for root user (client.root.crt, client.root.key)\n\nI could use CockroachDB's built-in `cockroach cert` commands, which would be simpler than raw openssl, but since we're working with an openssl-toolbox, I need to decide whether to use that toolbox or leverage the cert command from an existing pod.\n\nMy approach: spin up the toolbox pod (or use an existing CockroachDB pod) to generate the certificates, then create a Kubernetes secret with them. After that, I'll update the StatefulSet to mount the secret at `/cockroach/cockroach-certs`, remove the `--insecure` flag, add the `--certs-dir` parameter, switch the health probes to HTTPS, and restart the pods.\n\nWait, the prompt mentions an openssl-toolbox pod should be available, but it doesn't seem to be running yet. I'll exec into the existing crdb-cluster-0 pod to generate the necessary certificates using the cockroach cert commands, then create secrets from them and patch the StatefulSet to enable secure mode. I need to generate the CA certificate first, then the node and client certificates with the appropriate addresses.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":356,"cache_read_input_tokens":316